snippet.textDisplay: Truthfully, I like the home grown shows better than the studio ones. There's an honesty to the shows that is appealing. The guests look like real people, not plasticized perfect versions of themselves, their settings are interesting, the music is surprisingly good (enough) to still enjoy listening; it's got a more authentic quality and not auto-tuned/lip synched to death. The only thing I really miss so far is the house band. Feature segments from the band's musicians could add to the show.  Like the Formal Friday idea, highlighting ways to contribute or find assistance. Most of all, I like your frank monologue; you strike the right balance between entertainment and relevance with your authenticity, honesty and levity.

snippet.textDisplay:
My husband’s company has an international show every three years in Vegas. It was to end 3/13. Instead, it ended 3/12 and his company shut down for quarantine internationally. My husband, by his choice, stayed put. It would take another three weeks minimum for him to be able to make the three drive home. He cannot find an open restaurant, his Residence Inn took away the grills. He’s stuck without a way to get home.


Mind you, our town was was devastated March 2 and 3 with the Tennessee tornadoes. Less than three miles from home is devastation.

Crap, where am I? And where is this hand basket???
